{
  "doc_id": "9729",
  "text": "Enoxacin absorption was not influenced by milk. In previous studies, milk was found to lower the absorption of ciprofloxacin and norfloxacin by 33% and 48%, respectively [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , while the absorption of ofloxacin was not impaired by concomitant ingestion of the same volume of milk [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Similar results were obtained with yoghurt [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
